Nova Ljubljanska May Need $570 Million Capital Boost, Delo Says

-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 
2011-09-02T06:30:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/nova-ljubljanska-may-need-570-million-capital-boost-delo-says.html
Nova Ljubljanska Banka d.d.,
Slovenia’s biggest bank, may need as much as 400 million euros
($570 million) of fresh capital, Delo newspaper  reported  without
saying where it obtained the information.  The European Bank for Reconstruction and Development,
International Finance Corp., the financing arm of the  World
Bank , and Belgium’s  KBC Groep NV (KBC) , the second-largest investor in
the Slovenian bank, are set to participate in the capital boost,
according to Ljubljana-based newspaper.  Nova Ljubljanska may report a 2011 loss of as much as 80
million euros, Delo said.  NLB as the lender is known needs to raise capital after the
central bank IN Slovenia demanded it improves its capital ratios
by the end of the year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  